This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with zero-shot learning in image classification tasks. It also involves learning a projection function between feature space and semantic embedding space, which is a common technique in computer vision. Additionally, the paper mentions four benchmark datasets related to image classification. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as autoencoders and considers the relationship between feature classes and semantic classes, which suggests it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. 

The paper also involves natural language processing techniques such as semantic embeddings, which suggests it could belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions multi-modal datasets, which suggests it could belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
